item.title: XPN Local - 12.27.2022
item.description: For the last episode of WXPN Local in 2022, we take a look back at the Key Studio Sessions that stood out over the past year, from Mobbluz to Echo Kid. Broadcast on Tuesday, December 27, 2022.

item.title: XPN Local - 1.3.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session from John Train, new music by Andorra, Queen Jo, Chill Moody, and more, plus a preview of lots of January concerts on the WXPN Local show from January 3, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 1.24.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session from Moustapha Noumbissi, new music by INJI, Ajay, Ivy Sole, Caring Less and more, plus a spotlight on Eagles-centric songs from Philly artists, and a G. Love throwback on the WXPN Local show from January 24, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 1.31.2023
item.description: New music by Honeythunder, Ron Gallo, Ivy Sole and more on the WXPN Local Show, January 31st, 2023.

item.title: XPN Local - 2.7.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session from emospacebird., new music by XIIIM, Mochi Robinson, Loose Panic and ore on the WXPN Local show from February 3, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 2.14.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session double-header featuring V. Shayne Frederick and The Last Generation on Film, new jazz from Christian McBride and Michelle Lordi, new yeehaw from Mandy Valentine and Cosmic Guilt, and so much more on the WXPN Local show from February 14, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 2.21.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session from Ryan Gilfillian, new music from Curtis Cooper, Static Shapes, Nicole Saphos Band, and so much more on the WXPN Local show from February 21, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 2.28.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session from Grocer, new music from Pine Barons, Kenya Vaun, Suzanne Sheer, and so much more on the WXPN Local show from February 28, 2023!

item.title: XPN Local - 3.7.2023
item.description: A Key Studio Session with Ajay, a chat with Re-Mus, new music by Greg Mendez, Black Buttafly, The Menzingers, Alexis Cunningham and more on the WXPN Local Show from March 7, 2023.
